<ol class="mw-references references" typeof="mw:Extension/references" about="#mwt1352" data-mw='{"name":"references","attrs":{"group":"","responsive":"0"},"body":{"html":""}}'><li about="#cite_note-name-1" id="cite_note-name-1"><span rel="mw:referencedBy"><a href="./Achaemenid_Empire#cite_ref-name_1-0"><span class="mw-linkback-text">1 </span></a><a href="./Achaemenid_Empire#cite_ref-name_1-1"><span class="mw-linkback-text">2 </span></a></span> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-name-1" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation book" id="mwBoY">A. Shapour Shahbazi (2012).  Daryaee, Touraj, ed. <i id="mwBoc">The Oxford handbook of Iranian history</i>. Oxford: Oxford University Press. p.<span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwBog">Â </span>131. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier" id="mwBok">doi</a>:<a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="//doi.org/10.1093%2Foxfordhb%2F9780199732159.001.0001" id="mwBoo">10.1093/oxfordhb/9780199732159.001.0001</a>. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number" id="mwBos">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwBow">Â </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/978-0-19-973215-9" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-19-973215-9" id="mwBo0">978-0-19-973215-9</a>. <q id="mwBo4">Although the Persians and Medes shared domination and others were placed in important positions, the Achaemenids did not â€“ could not â€“ provide a name for their multinational state. Nevertheless, they referred to it as Khshassa, "the Empire".</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Oxford+handbook+of+Iranian+history&amp;rft.place=Oxford&amp;rft.pages=131&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2012&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1093%2Foxfordhb%2F9780199732159.001.0001&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-19-973215-9&amp;rft.au=A.+Shapour+Shahbazi&amp;rfr_i